A close-up studio product visualization cross-section cutaway detailing the multi-layer material skin of a fully assembled tactical wingsuit flight chassis. The outermost layer is a 1.5mm active chameleon stealth skin composed of flexible transparent hydrogel containing micro-etched vertical rows of shifting 130nm guanine nanocrystals. Directly beneath rests an amber-colored 1.0mm triboelectric fluoropolymer mesh with visible micro-ridges. The structural core shows a thick, matte-black aerospace-grade carbon fiber polycarbonate weave showing integrated micro-fluidic bus loops filled with high-conductivity liquid gallium alloy. The innermost face reveals a thick compliant, dark teal internal lining loop, realistic studio overhead cross-lighting, photorealistic material and resin textures, 8k --ar 16:9
